verbose_text: This observation clearly indicates that the luminescent characteristics of the FOLED are solely ascribed to molecular exciton formation within the F8BT layer, since exciplex and charge transfer exciton formation are strictly suppressed by both tunneling / thermionic injection of holes at the PEDOT :P SS/F8BT interface and enhanced hole transport.
